We have a [page|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF31/Form+Field+Markup+for+Templates] that explains how to create templates, and a big empty white space on the right side of the Create Template page. It would be helpful if we added a link in so people have a reference when creating a template.

When inserting a widget macro via the macro browser the result contains an empty macro body which renders strangely - see attached image.

I can replicate the problem by entering the following wiki markup:
{code}
{widget:url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZFD01r6ersw}
{code}
and then moving to the Rich Text editor tab.

I'm seeing this a lot in our logs:
{noformat}
2010-04-11 20:35:45,690 WARN [http-j2ee.node0.extranet.atlassian.com%2F172.16.3.10-8443-26] [com.opensymphony.xwork.DefaultActionInvocation] executeResult No result defined for action com.atlassian.confluence.pages.actions.HeartbeatAction and result input
 -- url: /json/startheartbeatactivity.action | userName: mwatson | referer: https://extranet.atlassian.com/pages/editpage.action?pageId=1827637358 | action: startheartbeatactivity
{noformat}

The method called by startheartbeatactivity doesn't look like it returns "input" but it clearly does.

