If Confluence is configured to delegate User logins to JIRA's user provider, and the 'External User Management' property is configured as 'ON', if an Administrator administrates either their own account, or a user's account, they are able to change the password. The UI reports 'Password Change Successful', however, no change is made.

This appears to be as Confluence does not implement password changes passing through to JIRA from Confluence; user management needs to be performed within JIRA.

