The process for uploading our javadoc to docs.atlassian.com is ridiculously manual and error prone.  This can, I believe, be fixed using maven 2's site plugin.

We should also be uploading javadoc with every milestone release, since often we change APIs early to allow plugin developers to account for the changes.

If a custom authenticator tries to addMembership for a user that is logging in (a common scenario for SSO authenticators) and confluence global permissions don't allow anonymous to use confluence the addMembership call fails with: 

{code}
com.atlassian.confluence.core.InsufficientPrivilegeException: User [Anonymous] does not have the required privileges.
	at com.atlassian.confluence.user.DefaultUserAccessor.addMembership(DefaultUserAccessor.java:81)
{code}

